A RESOLUTION
1 Urging increased state autonomy to allow for the creation of innovative solutions to work
2 disincentives and the reform of social safety net programs; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, according to Area Development, Georgia ranks first among all states as the best
4 state for business; and
5 WHEREAS, CNBC ranked Georgia number one in the United States for business
6 environment; and
7 WHEREAS, Georgia's economic strength and social capital foster an environment of
8 opportunity that benefits families striving to escape poverty; and
9 WHEREAS, Georgia's uniquely successful approach of integrated welfare program
10 enrollment via the Georgia Gateway has proven effective and paved the way for further
11 enrollment integration; and
12 WHEREAS, the State of Georgia has made concerted and significant efforts to identify and
13 address instances of chronic or inter-generational poverty that still occur among its citizens;
14 and
