56 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the members of this body urge the President and
57 Congress to streamline and consolidate reporting requirements from the states to the federal
58 government to save taxpayer dollars and yield efficiencies.
59 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the members of this body call upon the President and
60 Congress to embrace the principles of federalism to further empower states to be the
61 laboratories of democracy and drive innovative reforms and improvements to our nation's
62 social safety net.
63 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
64 and directed to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to
65 Georgia's congressional delegation, the Office of the President of the United States, the
66 Speaker of the United States House of Representatives, the Majority Leader of the United
67 States Senate, the United States Department of Health and Human Services, and the United
68 States Department of Agriculture.
